title: Pain Relief Network Typographic Logo
content:
New identity for NY client Pain Relief Network.   
Type is based on Bilak's Fedra which I intend to   
use for body copy on future collateral. difference between top and bottom is "T" . I did 2-4 versions of just about all the letters (except the O), and chooses these for final version. ![PRN logo type](http://web.archive.org/web/20050526120947im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/29/24650.jpg)
author: designalchemy

comments.content:
Pretty nice.   
I like the bottom "T".   
But the "W" isn't working - try a form like two "U"s.   
   
hhp

The 'E' looks slightly backslanted, and it lacks the   
'flair' you have in 'R' and 'K', for example. I prefer   
the bottom 'T' too. And I agree that 'W' looks out of   
place.
